(594, 64, 77, 5, 'Destroyed \n By: Pepper Winters (Goodreads Author) \n ***** 5 Killing Stars***** \n Give me a second to fully digest everything I just read....umm... WOW ... there are no words to describe how this book made me feel. The tragic story of Roan \"Fox\" was simply the most heartbreaking thing ever. So when reading this book, make sure to prepare your hear, grab a box of tissues and be prepared to cry your eyes out. \n \"The moment I set eyes on her, I tasted a delicious combination of fear and strength. Weakness and bravery, sadness and resignation. Instincts and needs that I\'d buried and ignored volcanoes to the surface. I lost control. I broke every rule and I didn\'t give a fuck. She woke a part of me I didn\'t know existed, layered in ice and cold blooded disassociation.\" \n Roan \"Fox is a tortured soul who has lived a horrible life at the hands of the worse kind of people, who kidnapped and held him captive since he was six years old. He was beaten and tortured into conditioning to doing everything and anything they wanted including kill. \n \" No one would look at me and think I was slave. But I had been. I still was. I probably would be forever.\" \n Once he finally escapes he begins to live as a zombie version of himself, unable to touch or be touch, unable to please or be pleased, simply miserable, living a life void of emotions and filled with fear. That is until he meets Hazel Hunter and his miserable life changes forever. \n \"I\'ll give you two hundred thousand for one month of pure access. I want to buy your obedience, your body, your mind. But most of all I want to buy your secrets.\" \n \" Tonight, I did the one thing that made least sense of all. I bought a girl. And I would never let her go.\" \n \"Top rule. Unbreakable rule. Don\'t. Ever. Touch. Me.\" \n He begins to fight all his conditioning instincts to be a \"normal\" man for her. But as with everything in his life, nothing is ever that easy. The road to normalcy is not as easy as he thought it would be after only one look into Zel\'s eyes at his club. \n \" You\'re Mine, and I refuse to live without you.\" \n The battle with his own personal demons wasn\'t so easily won. He has to challenge himself again and again with fear of losing the only people he loves. \n \"Obey or I\'ll kill you.\" \n \"I\'m here for you, for her. Forever if you\'ll have me. Just please-forgive me.\" \n Hazel \"Zel\" is a strong courageous woman, who fights with teeth and nail to save those she loves most. She instantly feels the connection between her and Fox and gives up herself in order to try to help him find his cure to his conditioning without losing her life along the way. But her secret can kill them both... \n \" No, I\'m not okay. Everything about you tells me to run, yet I ignore myself and end up getting hurt again. I find myself needing to help others-it\'s a compulsion driving me insane.\" \n \" You mistreat me, and I\'ll make you dickless for the rest of your life. Treat me with respect and desire and I\'ll stay. I accept your offer Obsidian Fox. Don\'t make me regret it.\" \n \" With fear and stupidity, I sold myself to him. Sold myself to a fighter who could sense my lies as easily as a fox senses a rabbit. \n I regretted it. I reveled in it. It destroyed me.\" \n Meanwhile she is also trying to save the life of the one person she loves most and she is afraid that in the end she will end losing them both. The life of her daughter, the life of the one person who has the ability to change everything. \n \"A child was my cure. The daughter of the woman I tried to kill. It was time to face my past full of darkness and say fuck you. It was time to start new memories.\" \n \"Her touch shattered me. Her touch awoke me. Her touch destroyed me.\" \n Their love is like no other, together they fight every instinct in their body, to run, to harm, to kill. He doesn\'t think he has what it takes to be a good man for her, and she can\'t give up on him, It\'s a love that fights all battles and has the ability to destroy them both. \n \" You are worthy. Every day I spend with you, your improving.\" \n \"Only because I keep my distance and don\'t touch you. Believe me, if you knew my thoughts you would run.\" \n \"Do you want me to run?\" \n \"You should.\" \n \"You own me, body and soul, Hazel Hunter. You\'re not just my lover but also my handler and I will walk over blades for you. I will kill for you. I will lay down my life for you.\" \n So, with nothing left to say other than YOU MUST READ this book!! You will Love Fox, you will also hate him but don\'t let that scare you in the end he makes it worth the wait but you need to read it to find out. \n **** For More Reviews Visit My Blog**** \n www.Jenreadit.com'),
