(604, 66, 29, 4, 'Layers Deep (Layers Trilogy #1) \n By: Lacey Silks (Goodreads Author) \n **** 4 Deep Stars **** \n One word... Cliffhanger!! Ugh, have I mentioned how much I hate cliffhanger? It\'s a bittersweet feeling because in a way it\'s good for the anticipation on what will happen next, but in this case NOT SO MUCH! Great read that may leave you blushing and wanting more... Now how can I explain my feelings about this book properly without giving too much away ??? \n \"Cross was too hot for his own good. I couldn\'t let his Zeus like looks and charming mouth derail my plans.\" \n \" Of course I liked him! Even Mother Teresa would have liked him.\" \n \"I don\'t sleep around, Allie. I\'m a one-girl kind of man.\" \n I think that pretty much covers it Right? Other than screaming HOT DAM!!!! \n So to Sum up, Allie needs Tristan for her Revenge Tristan needs Allie for his Rescue, the lines get blurred and things get OH SO INTERESTING!! \n \" Hit me.\" I could have sworn I\'d heard a slight growl in his voice. \n \"What?\" \n \"It\'s not a request. If you want me to consider you for the job you need to pin me to the floor.\" \n \"You just want me on top of you.\" I crossed my arms at my front. \n \" Actually I want you under me, and I wont have it any other way.\" He grinned \n I loved the story of Allie and Tristan, It was a mixture of the beginning of their love but also gave you an insight on one of the biggest worldwide issues we have today... SEX TRAFFICKING. Allie has to go under cover to get sold as a sex slave in order to try to save Tristan\'s ex from being sold. It was crazy to see the reality of sex trafficking. As much as I hated reading about what some of the women went through in the book, because I know it\'s a reality in our lives more than we\'d like it to be, it was a good way of showing the readers what many women out there are going through. \n \"If I had a choice I wouldn\'t hire you. I\'d keep you far away from the scum we\'ll be dealing with. But you\'re too perfect for the job. You\'re beautiful, smart and strong.\" \n But on a lighter note... Allie and Tristan Cross were a great pair. They completed each other\'s every need with trust in each other from day one. The chemistry between these two simply left me fanning myself... \n \"Cocky a bit? \n \" I guess you\'ll have to wait and see. \" \n \"You\'re unbelievable.\" \n \" I Know. And I\'m glad you know it, too. \" \n \"Have you always been a tease Allie? Or is it just for me? \n \"What?\" \n \"You say one thing but mean something else. I can see the way your body\'s reacting to me.\" I mean come on... What can you really say to that? \n \" You look beautiful when you blush.\" \n \" You should get off me.\" I felt my muscles tense.\" \n \"I should, and I will, but know that I don\'t want to.\" WOW!!! \n \" You taste much better than I imagined.\" \n \"Imagined?\" \n \"I wondered about your lips all night and couldn\'t sleep. Now I don\'t have to wonder anymore.\" \n \"I\'m glad I satisfied your curiosity.\" \n But as much as Allie tried to keep their relationship strictly professional it only worked for about 2 seconds. It was great to see the sparks between these two. Because honestly with a guy like Cross I don\'t really blame her! \n \" I\'d tasted forbidden fruit I couldn\'t get enough of. And I wanted more, I needed more.\" \n \" Mr. Impossibly hot could not only make me swoon in bed, but also in his kitchen.\" \n \" You perv! We\'re supposed to be exercising.\" \n \" Believe me, my heart gets a better work out when I look at you.\" \n So, Like I said I hate Cliffhangers, therefore I need more of Tristan!! Like NOW !! So keep posted for the second installment \"Layers Peeled\". Can\'t WAIT!! \n ****For more Reviews Check out my Blog**** \n www.Jenreadit.com'),
(605, 66, 46, 3, '***3.5 Stars*** \n Ok so under normal circumstances Nick would be all kinds of creepy for watching Daisy. But looking at it as a fictional perspective.... It\'s still odd but once you read on and get to know Nick you understand that in a way he doesn\'t know any better. \n \"I was born a killer, my teeth bared, and I claimed my first victim almost before I had taken my first breath. But that is Ukraine. A boy on the streets without a gun is prey. I have never been prey. Always the hunter.\" \n \"It takes many muscles to smile, more to frown, but only few to pull the trigger.\" \n Of course being the main characters and all you can\'t help but fall in love with Nick and Daisy. To watch both of them get over their fears and discover life together. \n \"There is something so vibrant, so aware, so alive about him that it sings to me. I am drawn to him like a moth to a flame.\" \n \" I will kiss you Daisy. I will kiss you all night. I will do more than kiss you if you wish.\" \n Daisy has just escaped her father\'s prison and Nikolai is attempting to free himself from the only life he knows, at the same time they are trying to build their first relationship. \n Neither one of them knows what to do, what\'s right and wrong in a relationship. But together they work on building their trust and love for one another even through the obstacles their old insecurities and fears throw their way. \n \" I knew I could not keep you,\" he says. His voice is hoarse with emotion. \"Such a beautiful, innocent soul. I just wanted you for as long as I could have you. I knew it was wrong, and I did not care. Someday I hope you forgive me.\" \n There were times I just wanted to shake some sense into Daisy, and there were times that I also wanted to tell Nikolai to Man up but I did enjoy learning about them. \n \" The villains had a hard life. They did not know any other way forward.\" \n \" I can\'t hate Nick. I\'m still hopelessly in love with him. \n With the bad guy. \n I wonder what this makes me.\" \n I am not going to lie, it\'s an interesting read, it\'s not usually my favorite kind but I thoroughly did enjoy reading it. Would I recommend it? Yes, I definitely would. \n \" I love Nick for who he is, Not what he is.\" \n \"See the truth in my eyes and know I do this for you.\" But whatever you decide, Kitten, I will support you.\" \n Their love for one another despite all their struggles is so captivating, that it makes it hard to explain.. So I\'ll just let their own words do the explaining... \n \"Spasiba.\" \n \"Why do you thank me?\" \n \"For caring enough to care about how I feel.\" \n \"I do not think you realize, Daisy. You are everything to me.\" \n \" Every day that passes, I love Nick more and more. I don\'t care about his past. We will build our own future, together.\" \n \" We\'re both patient people, Nick and I. We know how to wait, there\'s pleasure in the waiting.\" \n So Read it, Trust Me you will enjoy it!! \n *******For More Reviews****** \n www.Jenreadit.com'),
(606, 66, 46, 4, 'CUTE'),
(607, 66, 48, 5, '***** 5 AMAZING STARS \n Ruin \n By: Rachel Van Dyken \n I ABSOLUTELY LOVED THIS BOOK!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! \n I laughed out loud, Smiled myself silly, and Cried my eyes out, but LOVED every single minute of it!!! \n I can\'t stress this enough but I LOVED, LOVED, LOVED the story of Wes and Kiersten. \n It\'s an Amazing MUST READ! \n It will leave you so caught up in emotions that you will be speechless and thinking about this book for weeks.... Trust me!! \n \"I turned around... and ran smack dab into a tree. \n Or at least it felt like a tree. \n But trees weren\'t warm. \n And they didn\'t have one, two, three, four, six, Good Lord, eight? Eight packs? Furthermore, had I actually been feeling said person\'s eight pack? And, dear God, I was counting. I had touched each muscle. And great, my hand was still firmly placed against the guy\'s stomach. \n I jerked my hand back and closed my eyes. \n \"Were you just counting my abs?\" \n I think that in itself is enough said about Wes don\'t you think? How can you not fall in love with him? \n His eyes held my ruin. \n \"Weston.\" He held his hand . \"And you are?\" \n Screwed Kiersten.\" \n \" I seriously couldn\'t stare at him in the face; that was how gorgeous he was. I\'d never seen such a good looking guy in real life before. Sure, I\'d seen them on magazines and movies, but this guy... He was living breathing, walking sex. And considering I had no experience in that department, I was putting up every wall I could think of in order to remember to breathe.\" \n I loved their instant connection and hilarious, heartwarming banter. I couldn\'t help but smile almost the entire time. \n \"I don\'t get it. I could have sworn the freshman RA was a female.\" \n \"Sex change\" Weston said with a straight face. \" I was a confused child.\" \n \" Funny.\" I rolled my eyes. \"Seriously? I requested an all girls dorm and got put in a co-ed building, and then my RA is a --\" I was going to say hot guy by refrained from embarrassing myself. \n \"Sex god.\" He said it for me. \" I know, some people have all the luck.\" \n I am struggling to write a review for this without giving too much away and ruining the suspense for you so I think it\'s easier to let the characters speak for themselves... \n Lisa and Gabe were simply HILARIOUS!! I think everyone needs a roommate and friends like Lisa and Gabe. \n My screaming broke a lamp?\" \n \"No.\" She shook her head. \" My fall broke the lamp. Seems jumping out of your bunk bed at one in the morning\'s a contact sport. My lamp being the main target. No worries. She sighed. \" It didn\'t suffer. It shattered on contact with the floor. And then again after I slipped on the teddy bear that also fell. And that\'s great since it broke my fall onto the floor, making it so I escape with two faint bruises. \" \n \"Holy crap! I\'m so sorry!\' \n \"Nah, it\'s fine. I\'m a walking accident.\" She laughed. \" But if you plan on screaming all night, I\'m taking the floor. My lamp killing days are behind me.\" \" Oh and I sleepwalk so if you wake up to me standing over you, try not to punch me in the face. \" \n \"Wow, we\'re sure the fun pair.\" \n And then there is the fact that Wes is keeping a major bomb from Kiersten (spoilers) \n \"I was keeping something epic from her, which sort of made me the villain in this tale. But damn, I wanted to be the hero.\" \n \"For the first time in a year, I wanted to live -- because I wanted to spend every freaking day watching her open her eyes to the world. Hell, I wanted to be the first thing she saw. Sometimes, reality\'s a bitch.\" Enough said... \n So yes Read this book, Love it, Devour it!! \n It\'s just that good!! \n But before you do be sure to get comfortable, make sure you are alone , be prepared to not sleep and definitely have the tissues ready!! \n \"I can tell you have a good heart... because the minute I met you, I wanted to fight for it.\" \n She was silent. \n \"That\'s how you can tell when someone has a good heart... when you want to be the one to make it beat.\" \n \"I want all of your heart, even the broken pieces, the shredded ones that no longer fit. I want all of them - all of you. I need it all.\" SWOOOON \n http://jenreadit.com/ruin.html'),
(608, 66, 26, 3, 'Fun read! But I must say... with that ending, there better be another book coming soon!!'),
